# ── ListingLabs deploy repo — SECURITY-FIRST WHITELIST ───────────────────────
# The repo root is the `verifysheet` folder, but ONLY the folders the site build
# needs are tracked. Everything else here stays private and is NEVER uploaded.
# This whitelist is the guard: nothing outside the paths re-included below can be
# committed by accident, even if you run `git add .`.

# 1) Ignore EVERYTHING at the repo root first...
/*

# 2) ...then re-include only what the build needs.
#    (No trailing slash on the negations — that form reliably re-includes the
#     directory AND its contents across git versions.)
!/perps_correlation
!/cache
!/.github
!/.gitignore
!/README.md

# 3) Inside those folders, still drop noise and anything secret-shaped
#    (defense in depth — secrets live outside the repo, but never take chances).
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.ipynb_checkpoints/
**/*.env
**/secrets*
**/*.key
**/*.pem
**/*credential*

# 4) Drop heavy / regenerated artifacts the live site doesn't need. Excluding the
#    logs + notebooks also shrinks the surface where a stray key could hide.
perps_correlation/Listinglabs.zip
# The built site is published as a Pages artifact every run (never read from git),
# so tracking it would just churn HTML into history forever.
perps_correlation/Listinglabs/
perps_correlation/*.log
perps_correlation/**/*.log
perps_correlation/*.ipynb
perps_correlation/*.docx
